Set Business Hours

Specify the hours when your support team is available to serve customers. This helps make your department's processes, such as escalations and milestones, more accurate.

Available in: Salesforce Classic, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Entitlements and milestones available in: Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud

To set business hours:
From Setup, enter Business Hours in the Quick Find box, then select Business Hours.
Click New Business Hours.
Type a name for the business hours.
Choose a time zone to associate with the business hours in the Time Zone drop-down list.
Set your business hours for each day of the week.
If your support team is available during the entire day every day of the week, select the 24 hours checkbox.

You can also make the Business Hours field available on the Case Layout page so that your support agents can set the times a support team is available to work on the case.

Guidelines for Setting Business Hours
To make your support processes more accurate, define when your support team is available to help customers. There are a few guidelines to keep in mind as you set business hours:
Make sure your business hours accurately reflect when your support team is available.
Use specific time zones and locations to apply business hours to milestones, entitlement processes, cases, and case escalation rules.
Leave the business hours start and end times blank and the 24 hours checkbox deselected to indicate that the support team is not available at all that day.
title: Setting Business Hours for Service Cloud
